</taxonomicName>
, with a habi- tus comparable to those shown in figs. 811, 851; total length is given as 
<quantity box="[1045,1118,1528,1551]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="212.[701,1230,1499,1756]" pageId="212" pageNumber="213">
The shape of the opisthosoma is like that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="HUBER" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName=": Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[737,983,1587,1610]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneomaculatus">
